AgC, Bo, Sk record the same for Central QWS. Fi, Hy record the same for South QWS. Refers to 'pato quetro'. Of the many names for 'duck', this term is the only one occurring in all three dialect areas.

From English 'horse'. Bo, Sk, Fe record [oraɬe].
From Span. 'oveja'. Bo, Sk record the same for Central QWS. Also pakya.
From Span. 'vaca'.

Bo, Sk, Fe record the same for Central QWS. Also 'female' 02.240. With nouns of fem. gender (human or supernatural), the suffix -seles occurs in North, Central (Bo, Sk), and South (Fi, Hy). See 'sun, moon, star'.
Bo, Sk record the same for Central QWS. SpS records the same for South QWS. All mean 'husband' also.
Bo records c̷awɬ-kyekal for Central QWS.
Bo records kwoy-kyekal for Central QWS. SpS records okakɬ for South QWS.
Also means 'I' 02.910. Bo records aloks-kyekal for Central QWS. SpS records xaloks for South QWS.

Also means 'you (plural)'; and 3rd person, sg. and pl. Bo, Gui record c̷awɬ for Central QWS, which also means 'he/she'. SpS records c̷aw for South QWS.
Also means 'we' 02.940. Sk, Bo record c̷eɬ for Central QWS. SpS records c̷o for South QWS.

Also means 'family'. Also yerwaske. Bo records c̷ekweyko for Central QWS.

Refers to 'paternal grandmother'. Em records apanap-seles for 'maternal grandmother'. Bo records afkyaw-ses for Central QWS. Fi, Hy record kowe-seles for South QWS. Cf. 'grandfather' 02.460.
From Em, who also records oykem-na. Bo, Gui record oykep for Central QWS. Fi, Hy record kerowes for South QWS.
Em records kyewos 'paternal grandfather'; and apanap 'maternal grandfather'. Bo records afkyaws for Central QWS. Fi, Hy record kowes for South QWS.

Bo records are-ses for Central QWS, cf. 'younger sister' 02.455. Fi, Hy record c̷olkel for South QWS, cf. 'older sister' 02.454.

SpS records enakapar for South QWS.
Bo, Be, Gui record are for Central QWS. Fi, Hy record are for South QWS. Cf. 'younger brother' 02.445.

Also means 'child'. Sk records teleksta for Central QWS. Fi, Hy, SpS record paral for South QWS.

Bo records arak for Central QWS. Fi, Hy record arek for South QWS. These forms also means 'male'.

From Ag. Sk, Bo, Fe record ayose for Central QWS. Fi, Hy record ana for South QWS.
Also Em records afksayna. Bo records elwalok for Central QWS. Fi, Hy record elwalok 'boy', for South QWS.
Suffix -seles, as in 'sun, moon, star, girl, daughter, ' etc. Sk, Bo, Fe record the same for Central QWS.
Bo records arak for Central QWS. Fi, Hy record arek for South QWS. Also means 'husband' 02.310.
SpC, Gui record eɬatap; AgC, Sk, Bo record serks for Central QWS. Fi, Hy, SpS record eɬarapes for South QWS.
Gus, Sk record akses for Central QWS. Fi records akyenes for South QWS.
Also means 'fire'. Sk, Bo, Cy, Li, Gui record kakas for Central QWS. SpS records afsar for South QWS.

Bo, Co, Sk record the same for Central QWS.In North and Central QWS, it also means 'piedra de sílex', which produces sparks when hit, for making fire. Also North and Central (Me), [faya], from English 'fire'.

Bo records oley for Central QWS. SpS records olay for South QWS.

Also means 'firewood'. Bo, Fe, SpC, Li record c̷ˀarkwes; Sk records statal for Central QWS, (cf. 'embers' 01.841). Fi, Hy, SpS record tetel for South QWS.
Bo records yelc̷epes; Sk records ekyaraɬe for Central QWS. Fi, Hy record akoraɬka for South QWS. 'Iceberg' is akyaarase in North QWS.
Em records yenc̷epes. Bo, Sk record akʰape for Central QWS. Cf. 'winter' 14.740. Fi, Hy, SpS record asawe for South QWS.
Neutral morpheme; no verb-noun differentiation. Also kapkas. Sk, Ir record apers; Bo, SpC record kapkas for Central QWS. Fi, Hy record kapkas for South QWS.
Also kyeplas; alaxar. Sk records c̷etas for Central QWS.
Bo, Sk record akatel for Central QWS. Fi, HY record orkwas for South QWS.
Cf. 'up' 12.080 and 'weave' 06.330. Bo, Li record the same for Central QWS. Gui records ayel, (cf. 'fog' 01.740). Hy records yel for South QWS.
Also means 'night' 14.420.
From Ag. Sk records kyoyes-kwal for Central QWS.
Bo, Sk record akayelek for Central QWS.
Also Ag records keyero, which means 'red' 15.660. Bo, SpC, Gui record takal for Central QWS. Fi, Hy record kayero for South QWS.
From Ag. Cf. 'light' 01.610.
Also yekapc̷ewe-k-seles, which also means 'moon'. Bo, Sk, SpC, Ca, Gui record kolas for Central QWS. Fi, Hy, Sps record konas for South QWS.

seles means 'female'. Cf. yekap-c̷ewe, 'toward evening'. Also arka-k-seles (cf. 'up' 12.080). Ag, Em record akyewe-k-seles (cf. 'dark' 15.630). Bo, Sk, Be, Gui record yekaps-alok for Central QWS. Fi, Hy, SpS record [konako], from Yagan, for South QWS. In North QWS, kyepanok refers to the moon as a mythical character.

Lit. 'day-(suffix)-female' 14.410 + 02.240. Also arka-k-seles, which also means 'moon'. Also ac̷e-ksta; ac̷ˀayes, which both mean 'hot'. Bo, Sk, Be, SpC, Gui record arx-alok for Central QWS. South QWS is [lom], from Yagan 'lam'.
arka means 'up' 12.080. Also astes-c̷ewe. Bo, Sk record arka for Central QWS. Fi, Hy record akowa for South QWS.
Also Em records alkareske. Bo, Sk, Co, Ca record kyeɬaw; AgC records kalkayeske for Central QWS. Fi, Hy, SpS record keɬaw for South QWS.

Also kskawa. Em records yetapkamena. Bo records yawar for Central QWS.

From Ag.

Also ksena. Bo records ayakta-akwel (ayakta, 'tide'), for Central QWS. Cf. 'large' 12.550. SpS records afɬak for South QWS.

Also means 'salt; salty; wet'. Bo, Sk, SpC, Gui record c̷apɬ for Central QWS. Fi, Hy, SpS record c̷amɬ for South QWS.

Also akc̷awes; akc̷o-lay. Bo records akc̷o-lay for Central QWS. AgC, Gus, Sk, Bo, Be, SpC, Cy record akc̷o-kwar for Central QWS. All these forms also mean 'drink'. Fi, Hy, SpS record c̷awas for South QWS.
From Ag. The latter morpheme means 'inside' 12.050.
From Ag. wes is 'earth, land' 01.210. Ag records aseras. Ag and Em give ktey; kolaf for 'beach'. Hy and Fi give [wanek] for South QWS, from Yagan 'wenekata'.
From Ag. Lit. 'earth-large' 01.210 and 12.550.
Bo and Sk record the same for Central QWS. SpS records yesewar-kʰar for South QWS. Em gives yesewor, North QWS for 'small island'.
From Em. Cf. 'up' 12.080.
From Ag.
Bo and Gui record the same for Central QWS. Cf. 'sky' 01.510; 'up' 12.080. Also wes-kʰar; cf. 'earth' 01.210.

Bo records kyapc̷akɬ for Central QWS. Hy records [pawntel] for South QWS, from Yagan 'pantel'.

Bo records the same for Central QWS. Fi and Hy record papˀe for South QWS. Cf. 'mud' 01.214.
Sk, Bo, Be, Gui record kala for Central QWS. Fi, Hy record anokwal for South QWS.

Also means 'darkness' 01.620. Also yakapc̷ewe, which also means 'get dark'. Bo, Be, SpC record akyowe; Sk records kɬepe, which also means 'dark', for Central QWS. Hy records ako; Fi, Hy record yolape for South QWS.
From Ag. Cf. 'day' 14.410. Sk, Bo record kala-ler for Central QWS.
From Ag. Cf. 'day' 14.410 and 'old man' 02.461.
From Ag. Cf. 'day' 14.410.

Sk, Bo record the same for Central QWS. North and Central forms also mean 'now'.
Also means 'yesterday' 14.490. Sk, Bo, SpC record alkwalak for Central QWS.

Also means 'tomorrow' 14.480.

From Span. 'domingo'.

Sk records the same for Central QWS, which also means 'snow'.
Also means 'warm, sun, good weather'. Sk records yakaxɬ for Central QWS.
Fi, Hy record oks for South QWS. Cf. 'fragrant' 15.250 and 'stinking' 15.260.

Bo records c̷apɬ for Central QWS. SpS records akes for South QWS. All forms also mean 'sea'.
From Ag, Em, also means 'listen'. Sk records tel-kyol for Central QWS. Fi, Hy record teles for South QWS.

Sk, Bo, SpC record kyero for Central QWS. SpS records tˀel for South QWS. Cf. 'yellow' 15.690.
Sk, SpC record arkʰar for Central QWS. North and Central forms also mean 'green.

Also kyepc̷es, which also means 'freeze'. Sk, Bo, Be, Gui record kyesas for Central QWS. Fi, SpS record kesas for South QWS.

Sk, Bo record aleksta for Central QWS. Fi records feayel for South QWS.

Means 'for sure, certain'.

From Ag.
Sk, Bo, SpC, Fe, Gui record aylaw; Bo records aa for Central QWS. Fi, Hy record oo for South QWS.

Also afsa-lay; afsa-kyar; afsa-kʰas; afsa-tawan; afsa-xak. Sk, Bo record kstey for Central QWS, cf. North kstey 'converse'. Fi, Hy record yakafta for South QWS.

Also means 'speak' 18.210.

From Em. Bo records c̷aloklo for Central QWS.

Cf. 'bark' 08.750, footnote. Sk, Fe record taykalka for Central QWS.
Also means 'paper'. Also [lewro], from Span. 'libro'.
Cf. 'house' 07.120, and 'big' 12.550. Ag records at-pe.

Cf. 'chief' yerwose; and alkserxe-na 'order'.

Bo, Si record salaska; Fi, Hy, SpS record senekye for Central QWS.

SpC records selekɬe for Central QWS. SpS records senekye for South QWS. All the forms means 'gun'. Cf. 'sling' 20.230. Bo records takal-kwa, 'cannon' for Central QWS, cf. 'thunder' 01.560, footnote.
From Ag. Bo records ales for Central QWS. Cf. 'run' 10.460, footnote; and 'flee' 10.510.
Also means 'short paddle'. Also Em records kyatel; and Ag records kwatal.
From Ag, Em. Bo records kyapla for Central QWS.
Also yektel; yefto-lay, which also means 'to throw a stick'. Bo records yepˀat for Central QWS.
Cf. 'throw a stick, hunt' yefto-lay; 'throw rocks' xowtas; 'to spear' akyar; kerkstes. Bo, Gui record kaynel; Bo records akyar for Central QWS. SpS records yeftela for South QWS.
Means 'trap for ducks'. 'Lasso, snare' to hunt ducks is tay. Sk records tay for Central QWS.
Cf. 'flame' 01.820.
Also means 'thief'. Bo, Gui record akwas for Central QWS.
Also means 'to steal'. Also lol-kwal. Bo records xekyalesor for Central QWS.
From Ag. Cf. 'sky' 01.510. Also Ag records yema-arkac̷ewe-c̷kes, cf. 'white man' yema. Bo records arka-kerc̷es.
From Span. 'padre'.
Also Ag records yeksolo. Bo records ale-kerkc̷es; tolwa; tokwato, 'malevolent spirits', for Central QWS.
